column6: Vietnam Rubber (Industry) Group provides technical, advisory, and consultancy services to the rubber industry. Its services enable the rubber industry to control and monitor the quality of rubber, rubber planting materials, and rubber products; develop, transfer, exploit, and promote research findings; sell and export crude natural rubber; supply and import inputs; and export machinery and spare parts. The company also produces technical specified and constant viscosity rubber; and latex, which is used to produce medical gloves and condoms. Vietnam Rubber Industry Group was founded in 1995 and is based in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.

Yunnan State Farms Group is a state-owned agricultural enterprise. It was founded in 1996 and is based Kunming, China

Convalt Energy engages in developing and acquiring energy generation assets. It focuses on solar energy; onshore and offshore wind development; hydro, waste to power, and gas fired thermal power plants. The company's activities also include developing energy transmission and distribution assets; and investment in existing operating assets worldwide. Convalt Energy was founded in 2010 and is based in NYC, New York.
Russia-based Grand Capital is a forex broker. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in Moscow, Russia.

General Electric (GE) produces aircraft engines, locomotives and other transportation equipment, kitchen and laundry appliances, lighting, electric distribution and control equipment, generators and turbines, and medical imaging equipment. GE is also one of the Unites States' pre-eminent financial services providers. GE Capital, comprising commercial finance and energy financial services, is its largest segment. GE's other segments are energy, technology infrastructure, and GE home & business solutions. The company was founded in 1892 and is headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts, US.
Boonthavorn Ceramics retails tiles, hardware, and other home building material. The company is headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand.
